347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.09cb5db1-9d45-49b1-8174-a5ec947d052a.description=This operation deploys the given Application's Version on the required target. It will return the details of DeploymentJob created for deploying the version. This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later. Inputs\: coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443' coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS' coreUsername - Username of the SA. corePassword - Password of SA user. coreVersion - [Optional] By default, it is the SA version being used. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. isAdmUndeployPreVersion - [Optional] Should the ADM undeploy the previous version of application? (y/n) By default it is 'y' timeout - [Optional] Job timeout in millisecond, If it is zero (0) then the given operation will return immediately. By default it is '20000' admJobComment - [Optional] Job Comment. Outputs\: status - Operation completion Status. idAdmDeploymentJob - ADM Id of Application Deployment job. admJobStatus - Status of Job. It could be one of [NOT_STARTED, CANCEL_PENDING, CANCELED, PAUSE_PENDING, PAUSED, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED, FAILED, ATTENTION_REQUIRED]. admJobComment - Job Comment. isAdmJobRollbacked - Is rollbacked? (y/n). isAdmJobUndeployed - Is Undeployed? (y/n) idAdmRollbackedJob - ADM id of Rollback Job. idAdmUndeployedJob - ADM id of Undeployed Job. admJobStagedDate - Application staged date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). Is available only for SA 9. admJobDeployedDate - Application deployed date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). admJobType - Type of Job. It could be one of [DEPLOYMENT, MAKE_VERSION, ROLLBACK, UNDEPLOYMENT]. idSaJob - SA Id Of SA Job. idAdmVersion - ADM Id of Application Version. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. idAdmRelease - ADM Id of Application Release. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. idAdmApplication - ADM Id of Application. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. idAdmTarget - ADM Id of Application Target. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. idAdmEnvironment - ADM Id of Application Environment. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. Responses\: success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'. failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'. 347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.0fb5ccbf-13ef-455b-a45a-035177e1c2df.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. 347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.16cbea8c-3131-41cc-b899-0775cc601098.description=This workflow returns the Resource provider details. Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.db7218c1-751f-4365-ade0-571b19602fb4.prompt=Process Instance ID 347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.ddb04225-0d98-4202-a6a4-efe801e4f532.prompt=Artifact ID 347d1032-5fa7-44b2-8a81-0448883b22a0.description=
This workflow performs MOE Add Server operation and deploys application into ADM identified by CSA Service Component

Inputs\:

CSA_CONTEXT_ID		- CSA Context Id
CSA_PROCESS_ID		- CSA Process Instance Id
SVC_COMPONENT_ID 		- This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
RSC_PROVIDER_ID		- This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL 	- This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID 		- This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
			   Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE		- This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
RSC_POOL_ID		- This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
SVC_INSTANCE_ID		- This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID		- This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
PRN_COMPONENT_ID		- This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
REQ_ORG_ID 		- This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
REQ_USER_ID 		- This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
USR_ORG_ID 		- This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
RSC_BINDING_ID 		- This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

These tokens with the default values are resolved by CSA when the flow is invoked.

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
